The paper focuses on emotion recognition using deep networks and attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The paper also discusses the use of adaptive fusion networks, which are a type of machine learning algorithm commonly used in large-scale data analysis (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of context in emotion recognition, which is a topic of interest in human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
